caption: Please see update at bottom for downgrade in star rating.  Had a fabulous experience at the Salt Factory Pub for lunch today! Upon entering, I was immediately greeted and shown to a table which is always a great first sign.  The entire staff was super friendly and attentive. The food was awesome! I ordered a hamburger and fries. Important to note...I have a serious medical condition and therefore am on a strict no added sodium diet. Oddly enough since the restaurant is called Salt Factory lol, but they were so wonderful about altering my food! Even without salt, the burger had such great flavor and depth. My friend had the Thai Beef Lettuce Wraps and loved them. Also loved the decor here! We will definitely return and I'm spreading the word to my friends about this great place!  COVID note: there are clear dividers between the tables and hand sanitizer was readily available.  All staff wore masks and we were easily distanced from other diners.  UPDATE 03/22/21: Returned for the third time on a Monday (we usually go on Wednesdays) and unfortunately, it was a very different experience. The wait staff was completely different, inattentive and not so friendly. We had to wait a considerable amount of time for them to take our order and ended up calling over the manager(?) to take it as our server never came back. The food quality was no where near what is was previously. We had to send our soup back. After two stellar experiences here, we were very disappointed.

Have been here several times always sit at bar with great service took a visitor there tonight and was very disappointed.  Waiter inattentive  unfriendly and acted as though we were a bother.    Extremely disappointed.   Our orders were wrong but ate them anyway.
Excellent experience
Good food and fast people are amazing

My wife and I always pass this restaurant and finally decided to stop by, we’re so happy that we did.  I’ll start off with the service, we were promptly seated and our waitress, Pegah, was so friendly, prompt, and helpful! My husband ordered an Arnold Palmer and they were out of lemonade for the night, so she hand mixed the drink with syrup and sweet tea, which was so thoughtful ! The manager was also very friendly and came around every so often to check on us, he also brought us a dessert because it was our first time( delicious btw) The food and drinks were awesome! We ordered the Louisiana burger, pulled pork tacos, and steakhouse burger, which were great and portion sizes were more than enough, very filling! we'll definitely be back and will be telling others to stop in for the full experience!!!!

Perfectly prepared fried okra w a sweet thai sauce to start. Excellent beer list. The Salt Factory Salad had fresh greens, tossed in a buttermilk dressing with fresh sweet tomatoes and heart of palm, not the same old salad. Best hanger steak my husband has eaten in years! Mashed potatoes were rich, buttery and creamy with just enough garlic. Delicious meal, exceptional service, from a locally owned restaurant.
Great service..clean! The food was awesome and arrived quick despite how busy they were👌
Service was great! Vast variety of food. Huge drink selections. Thumbs up all around.
Had a great experience this week for restaurant week. Everything was delicious, but the trout is a standout. I liked it as much as the pontchartrain at Flatlands.

Food is great! All the staff, very friendly and kind. It was clean, and family friendly. Also, you can see everyone wearing masks, which is very appropriate it on this times. The week menu has great options and very big portion. All we eat was great, probably the Shepherd's pie was slightly under seasoned, but as I said, everything was good, and the portions are very generous. We would definitely come back here!
The experience was great. Food fantastic!!!!!!
Enough food.
First time. Food was great. Had the blackened Mahi Mahi and risotto. Wife had the burger. Both were extremely good. Can't wait to go back.

Delicious, if not a touch expensive. The pulled pork tacos were fantastic and could've been a stand alone meal. Had the steak burger, cooked exactly as ordered. Staff was incredibly friendly and helpful as well. Will certainly make this a place for special occasions.
Excellent customer service and wonderful food! We will definitely go back again!
A little expensive. Their outdoor dining wasn’t working because they didn’t have gas for heaters

Ambience was good. Drinks were on point and food was tasty. I did think menu was rather limited. For vegetarians, it was just down to one of the three items aside from salads. From a service standpoint, I liked the speed and quality. I usually go for bar seating so I can enjoy a conversation with the bar staff. Not so here, as they kept to themselves. Also some bar staff weren't wearing masks - I docked one star for that given how important that is in these times.

Came here for dinner and drinks one night. I got the Mother of All Mimosas and loved it. I tried the butternut squash ravioli, however it was wayyyy too sweet. It needed something to cut the sweetness. It felt almost as a dessert. I got the margherita pizza and it was...meh. My fellow vegetarians: sorry, not too many options :(  I would probably come back for the drinks but not for the food.
Great food! Try it!
Great food and customer service!! Drinks looked good too!
Good drink selection, good burgers

Love eating outside. Fish n chips amazing. My hamburger twice has been way undercooked - raw in the middle which is not medium well. Fries are delish. Both last visits they didn’t bring cutlery until after the food came. I also ordered gluten free burger no bun but it came on a bun. Not sure if we will be back.
Every dish we had was amazing. The mussels were perfection and the desserts were awesome. The staff was courteous and we're very interested in taking care of us.
Excellent. I had the egg rolls as appetizer, the mussels were superb and plenty. My husband had the Mahi Mahi (was great but wasn't very fond of the side. - would change for another side).

We arrived early evening, one of only maybe 4 tables at the time. While all staff we interacted with were friendly,  service was very slow. We had the crabcake appetizer, the trout and fried chicken. The food was good but not great, some individual components were hot and some were not: hot crabcake cold stale frites on top, hot mashed potatoes cool gravy... Beer could have been colder. The table, menus, cutlery, and bathrooms were clean. Again, friendly staff but service was very slow.  We told our waiter about the stale frites and he just looked at us and said oh.  I had to order my 2nd beer twice.  It seemed the wait staff were too busy in the corner discussing something more important?  Our first time there, maybe they weren't having the best night. Lots of other places to choose from in Alpharetta with much better service.

Our first time here and everything was incredible! Sarah, the bartender, had a warm and friendly vibe. Everything we ordered was fresh and delicious. One of the best Old Fashions I've ever had! I will definitely be back and I'm only sorry that it took this long to try them out!

Nice meal,  solid burger and chicken fried steak, oysters were fresh and tasty,  calimari was tender and had a nice aoili and chopped pepper garnish (I wish it had more!)  Staff was friendly and attentive, food and drinks arrived in a timely manner.  We would return.

3 stars for the staff and the onion rings but extremely over priced for what it is. Dry burgers, wrong orders, strange drinks and cold soup. We won't be coming back but that's just us. The only thing that we would eat would be the burgers, were not seafood or pizza people so if you're into that please go try Salt. If you're going for burgers just go to South Main Kitchen up the street the burgers are great not as good as the Vortex on Moreland Ave. but really good! Good luck and happy hunting new places to try on the square in Alpharetta :)
My husband had the chicken pot pie, I liked it better than my Shepard's Pie (still good). He also enjoyed the Smoked Rose cocktail. Blue Moon is always good.

SO Delish!!! One of my favs and staples here in Alpharetta. Service is always perfect and the food is even better. I love how accommodating the management is at this location, they really go to the next level to make your experience that much better. Highly recommend.

I have been to many good places that make the 4 star rating. This place though, a solid 5 stars from me. The staff was very friendly and accommodating, especially with covid in full swing in GA. We jad a nice little nook outside to have lunch. I had the fish and chips. The fish was very fresh and tasted great. The slaw was out of this world and the fries were perfect. They were also the first restaurant I have been to that not only had ginger ale, but it was fresh and carbonated. My wife and mother in-law both had salads and the raved about them the whole time. The said the salads were the best they had and the loved their dressings. Then we did also have dessert as well. I had the brownie and my wife and mother in-law had creme brule. I tasted the creme brule and it was perfect. My brownie came with a scoop of vanilla ice cream and a little fudge. Hands down the best brownie dessert ever. I will be telling my friends about this place for sure. Great service, atmosphere and reaaonable prices. You can't go wrong. Absolutely worth going.
Great service and great food!

Their stuffed fried green tomatoes are the best I ever had.  Anywhere.  Made intricately by a very talented chef/owner.  I travel far to come here because it’s that delicious!  Can’t wait to see it back on the menu.  Please ;)

Outside patios are available for seating during warmer weather. Self parking or valet parking is available. This place is a decent discovery you should check out.

Great ambiance.  There were 4 of us, two couples that arrived on a Saturday at 7 with no reservations.  They put us on the list and the bar area was fairly busy but we were able to get some well mixed cocktails and a beer while waiting. We then got a table within 30 minutes and ordered with a savvy server.  She was efficient, helpful with the menu and timely.  We all ordered different entree's which were generally enjoyed.  The jambalaya and the Scallops were the favorite dishes.  The burger was good.  The shepherds pie was good but seemed less traditional that we expected.  Overall great experience we will be back.

Very warm atmosphere because of the soft and antique lighting. Nice restaurant layout with a long bar. Great service and the burger was very tasty. Great wine, beer, and cocktail selection. I will be back!
We love salt,  always great food and atmosphere!
Absolutely incredible!  I had the Chicken Fried Chicken and I will definitely be back for it again!  Friendly staff and excellent service!  Highly recommended!

We were in Atlanta on vacation and met some friends whom we hadn't seen in a while here as it was a good half way spot and the reviews were good. Well, let me add to those good reviews! The atmosphere here was relaxed and not too loud. Our waiter was very attentive but not hovering. When one in our party was indecisive he brought out a sample for her. We ended up staying for 4 hours catching up with each other - never felt rushed. We left a big tip (at least 40%) to hopefully make up for dominating the table. But the best part I haven't mentioned is the FOOD!! SO great!!!  I had their Sheppard's pie that they make with real lamb and not ground beef - DELICIOUS!!!  My husband had the She crab soup and I tasted it - so good!!  I just wish we lived closer as this would be my favorite restaurant to come to often!!
Delicious food!

The best crab soup I've ever had, and the belt was very good, but the server seemed a little off and the food sat poorly (not like I was sick, I just ordered really unhealthily I guess. Possibly to much bread and fried stuff?) all afternoon.
Nice spot. Great customer service and the food was good. Mussels had a rich thick sauce. The She Crab soup was perfectly seasoned and I could see and taste the small pieces of crab.

My colleagues and I visited on New Years Eve. We all enjoy our food and the service was phenomenal. I ordered the traditional burger, accompanied with fries, and it was delicious. Our server/waiter, Leo, was very attentive, friendly, and patient with us while ordering our food and deciding on beverages. He even brought us some Champaign at the end of the evening to celebrate the new Year. 5 Stars on my end.
Excellent

This place puts privately owned restaurants to shame! The service and attention to detail and concern from the staff was awesome and  we are still talking about the food 24 hours later.  Such a neat place to eat while we were in town! Will remember it and visit again when we can.
Excellent food. The Pork Tacos are absolutely outstanding!
Great food and drink menus.  Exceeded expectations.

I had been to the Roswell location and this one is equally as good. I've had fish, shepherds pie, chicken fried chicken, burgers, and appetizers here and I've never been disappointed by any of it. Solid whiskey and beers selection and great service.
This place is certainly nice. A little pricey but to be expected in downtown Alpharetta. Good cocktails and food though.
Food was great, service excellent. more on the expensive side for brunch but awesome food and portions are huge. diverse menu, especially for lunch/brunch. not overly crowded Saturday late morning.

We loved the food, wine and staff here. Matthew is absolutely the best!

Loved everything about this place! Service was amazing! Food was absolutely delicious. Ambiance was lovely. Perfect for a date night or grabbing a drink and bites with friends. Will definitely go back when I’m in town

This was a place that I'd been wanting to visit and never had the chance until today. I had the Shepard's Pie and my friend, James, had the traditional burger. We both enjoyed the meals and our waitress brought us a dessert creme brulee which was absolutely delicious. I'm bad with names but you know who you are.. She was adorable and very friendly. If anyone asks where to get a great meal at the right price I'm pleased to recommend the Salt Factory to any of my friends or family. I look forward to my next visit.
Nice place to sit and eat. I'm not a big fan of the items in the menu so can't give 5 stars
Nice menu and generous portions. Tasty!
Love poached pear salad
Really great staff. Even better food. Only gripe is that it's right next to a Taco Bell. I ordered the Blood Orange Salmon, it was freaking great. They had a decent mule too.

Visited for a Saturday lunch. My wife started with the Blueberry Bramble drink, which she thoroughly, enjoyed while I had a frosty cold beer. Her hot wings were tasty and my fried grouper sandwich was delicious.  Our waiter was courteous and attentive.
Staff here are awesome!  Food was really good and there was alot of it which evens out the price. Love the lighting and the bar. Looking for these lights for my home. 😂
I had a delicious burger, served by a very friendly and competent server.  Beware that the place can get very loud though.
Fun menu. Cool design and feel to the place. Food was delicious and of course the brew options were insane.
Great food and service

Food is decent. But IMO it's over-hyped and greatly over-priced. If you want someplace fancy where you get more food for your $, then personally I would opt for Village Tavern or a Brazilian steakhouse instead. Or possibly Sage.
Really cool place..great atmosphere and our waitress was great!
Service and food was very good also liked the atmosphere. This place is not too big not too small very cozy.
Good food and service.
Excellent. Liz our bartender/waitress was amazing. The food was delicious
Average
Great food and drinks. Friendly and kind staff.

The food here was the better part of this experience. I had a vege burger here and I have to admit that taste was really authentic. We tried few kinds of beers and for instance Mexican Pilsen Lager is very far from Pilsner beer, believe me I lived in Pilsen for many years. The waiteress really wasn't a pleasant one. Food was delicious! Sad to say the giant rowdy party table they sat right behind us didn't help the atmosphere though. No fault of the restaurant as there's no where else to sit that large of a group, but it made the evening very cramped and couldn't hear across the table.
Great first experience! Service was friendly. Atmosphere is nice. And food was delicious. I got the London broil and it was moist and tasty.

Lively neighborhood pub with very good food. Service was slightly slow due to July 4th crowd. Overall would recommend and definitely go back

They have this great burger that's called the beyond burger, which is a plant based burger. It's so yummy and I'm vegan so that was really an amazing find. Thank you salt factory your one my favorite places to go to when I'm in Alpharetta
Awful!!!! Service, time to get the food and the overall experience.  Our server Sam was a trainwreck.  We will never be back. Too many other options.
Never have had a bad meal never. Always phenomenal.   Good wine.  Good atmosphere. Highly recommend
Outstanding food and bar selection.  Great service as well.  Lots of good seafood including fresh Oysters from different regions.  Had a great time and enjoyed the restaurant.
Great place for a date!
Crab soup was great!

Food is very delicious and portion size varies greatly. I had fish of the day...very small, but savory while a friend had the largest fish sandwich you have ever imagined. I wish I thought to take a pic cause you wouldn't believe it! 🤣  The bread pudding is out of this world so save room!! Patio is nice when breezy and inside looks nice too. Service was super friendly, a tad slow but overall wonderful. Check it out and see for yourself.

Salt is by far one of my FAVORITE PLACES to eat .. Seriously, I would eat here 7 days a week if I could afford it, but alas I am not that a baller, so special treat eats is where they stand. At Salt I am 90% a creature of habit and eat the Ahi Tuna Tartare as my main course. It’s melt-in-your-mouth Ahi tuna with avocado and house made wonton crisps. Thanks to Salt I found my most FAVORITE WINE EVER which is Cherry Pie (Pinot Noir),  mmmm, delicious. They have several vegetarian options and many choices that are sure to spark interest in carnivores. My hubby enjoys the Shepherd’s Pie or Gastropub Burger with a glass of Disaronno (which is always a “perfect pour” per him). Staff are always, always, always friendly, even if the location is busy, and whether indoor or outdoor the general vibe of Salt is one that is hard to come by. Do recommend!

Had dinner with my mom, my future mother in-law and my fiance. Food was great as was the service for how busy they were. It was my mom's birthday and they definitely took great care of her, in a low-key way, which was awesome! The only negative I had was that there was mandatory valet parking in their main lot but their valet guy was super friendly and directed me to the street in the back which was more preferable for me. Would definitely visit again!
First and foremost, I've never been disappointed with the service here. This place is excellent. The Alpharetta Burger is fire and the oysters are always a great choice. Highly recommend this place!
Great service. Delicious food
Nice food.

The food was great snd the service was even better!  We had the Louisiana egg roll,  the london broil with HUGE onion rings, the blood orange glazed salmon over potatoes snd I had their Manhattan. Very pleased with our whole experience! We will be back again. Keep up the great work!
Southern favorites with a creative spin. Shrimp and grits is one of the best I've tried here. Great place for dinner on the weekend, large craft beer selection with lots of local brews.
The food is very good, as well as the serving. There is also valet parking.
Awesome burgers

We stopped in for something light.  The She Crab soup was excellent, with lots of crab in it.  The Crispy Shrimp and the Lettuce Wraps were terrific!  I would highly recommend each of those.  We'll be going back soon for a full meal.
Love this place...a little quirky, but great food, great service, great beer, and great atmosphere.
Amazing customer service!

Service, food, drinks, and atmosphere were all amazing!! We had the Louisiana egg rolls- lots of flavors that blended into something beyond words. Shepard's pie- the lamb inside was tender and flavourful. London broil- seasoned to perfection with a delicious crust. Blueberry bread pudding- delicious and not too sweet. Walk through the garden(I think it's name)- gin cocktail on the specials menu, created by the bartender. Wonderful drink. My boyfriend and I don't go out often, but this place was definitely somewhere we will return to again!

This was the second time I had been here and the experience was just as good as before.  The weather was so nice we sat outside. The manager even came out and checked on us as well as other guests.  I had a ribeye sandwich which tasted good but some of the pieces of meat in the sandwich were too large for a bite and a little difficult to bite off. I would end up with a mouth full of meat.  I would recommend this place.
Overall, a good experience. Service was good. Chicken and Waffles was decent. Worth a try, imho.
Great food and very good wait staff
Wonderful! Absolutely wonderful!
Very nice service and good food, I gave 4 stars because we were not asked for a second coctail til the end of the meal, Thank goodness our water glasses were refilled!
The butternut squash ravioli and the fried okra are to die for. Great whiskey menu!
High quality food. The chicken fried chicken is exceptional and the rest of the menu is good as well. Good service.

F Excellent bar service.   My wife and I stopped in for a cocktail and light meal the other night.  We sat at the bar and couldn't have asked for a better time.  The bartender was friendly and knowledgeable and made our drinks perfectly.  We ordered the Butcher Block (charcuterie board) and not only were all of the items delicious, but the portions were more than generous.  There is an extensive bourbon and beer list and the only thing I found to complain about was that they placed a Terrapin (Miller) beer tap in the middle of their local craft beer section. Salt, if Salt is the Answer, I Want More!!!  Do you like a large selection of Bourbon & Scotch? Do you enjoy a huge variety of domestic and foreign craft beers? Do you yearn to learn more about the world of rare spirits and seek expert advice?  Then your first stop is the bar and say hi to Liz. She will guide you to the best spirit or beer. Looking to experiment, maybe those previous Scotchs were WAY too smoky? She can lighten that up for you or recommend a sugary bourbon to go with your nice filet.  Speaking of selection, I was blown away by the rare spirits on hand. Keep in mind, I refer not to "Blue", "Black", or "Red" label stuff. I'm talking about the secret stuff you never experienced that costs half as much.  Here are a couple spirits to absolutely experience while at Salt Factory.  1. Balvenie Double Wood 14 Year - Legendary single malt from Speyside and rare find at a bar.  2. Monkey 47 - Legendary Gin from the Black Forest of Germany. Yes, 47 botanical ingredients grown deep in the mythical Black Forest of Germany. Best as a dry martini, that only sees but does not touch the bottle of vermouth!  Note to Management - Liz is a keeper and her knowledge along with incredible customer service puts her in a unique position to help guide the choices of spirits at Salt Factory.
